{"title_page": "58th Ariel Awards", "text_new": "{{Use mdy dates|date=January 2017}}\n{{Infobox film awards\n| number           = 58\n| award            = Ariel Awards\n| image            = Official Poster - Ariel Awards 2016.jpg\n| caption          = Official poster\n| date             = May 28, 2016\n| site             = [[National Auditorium]]<br>[[Mexico City]], Mexico\n| host             = \n| producer         = \n| director         = \n| best_picture     = ''[[The Chosen Ones (2015 film)|Las Elegidas]]''\n| most_wins        = ''Las Elegidas'' and ''[[Gloria (2014 film)|Gloria]]'' (5)\n| most_nominations = ''[[The Thin Yellow Line|La Delgada L\u00ednea Amarilla]]'' and ''Gloria'' (14)\n| network          = [[Canal Once (Mexico)|Canal Once]]\n| duration         = \n| ratings          = \n| last             = [[57th Ariel Awards|57th]]\n| next             = [[59th Ariel Awards|59th]]\n}}\n\nThe '''58th Ariel Awards''' ceremony, organized by the [[Academia Mexicana de Artes y Ciencias Cinematogr\u00e1ficas|Mexican Academy of Film Arts and Sciences]] (AMACC) took take place on May 28, 2016, at the [[National Auditorium]] in [[Mexico City]]. During the ceremony, AMACC presented the [[Ariel Award]] in 26 categories honoring [[2015 in film|films released in 2015]]. The ceremony, was televised in Mexico by [[Canal Once (Mexico)|Canal Once]].<ref name=Ariel-Nominees-2016>{{cite news|url=http://www.cinepremiere.com.mx/58431-nominados-al-ariel-2016.html|title=Nominados al Ariel 2016|date=April 13, 2016|accessdate=April 13, 2016|work=Cine Premiere|last=Maga\u00f1a|first=Arturo|language=Spanish}}</ref>\n\n''[[The Chosen Ones (2015 film)|Las Elegidas]]'', and ''[[Gloria (2014 film)|Gloria]]'' each won five awards, with the former earning the [[Ariel Award for Best Picture|Best Picture]] honor. Other winners included ''[[El M\u00e1s Buscado|Mexican Gangster: La Leyenda del Charro Misterioso]]'' with four; ''[[600 Miles|600 Millas]]'', and ''El Hombre Que Vio Demasiado'' with two; and ''Ausencias'', ''[[Embrace of the Serpent|El Abrazo de la Serpiente]]'', ''[[El Jerem\u00edas]]'', ''Hilda'', ''La Incre\u00edble Historia del Ni\u00f1o de Piedra'', ''[[Un Monstruo de Mil Cabezas]]'', ''Tr\u00e9mulo'', and ''Zimbo'' with one.\n\n==Winners and nominees==\nThe nominees for the 58th Ariel Awards were announced on April 13, 2016 at the Cineteca Nacional in Mexico City, by [[Dolores Heredia]], president of the Academy, and actors [[Adriana Paz]] and [[Juan Manuel Bernal]], winners for Best Actress and Best Actor, respectively, at the [[57th Ariel Awards]].<ref name=Ariel-Nominees-2016/> ''[[The Thin Yellow Line|La Delgada L\u00ednea Amarilla]]'' and ''[[Gloria (2014 film)|Gloria]]'' received the most nominations with fourteen; ''[[600 Miles|600 Millas]]'' and ''[[The Chosen Ones (2015 film)|Las Elegidas]]'' came in second with thirteen apiece.<ref name=Ariel-Nominees-2016/> The [[Golden Ariel]] was awarded to actress [[Rosita Quintana]] and film director [[Paul Leduc (film director)|Paul Leduc]].<ref name=Ariel-Nominees-2016/> The ceremony was held at the [[National Auditorium]] in Mexico City for the first time, instead of its traditional venue, [[Palacio de Bellas Artes]], in order to increase the capacity to 2,300 seats, according to Heredia.<ref name=Ariel-Nominees-ElUniversal>{{cite news|url=http://www.eluniversal.com.mx/articulo/espectaculos/cine/2016/04/13/anuncian-cintas-nominadas-al-ariel-2016|title=Anuncia cintas nominadas al Ariel 2016|date=April 13, 2016|accessdate=April 19, 2016|work=El Universal|last=Huerta|first=Cesar|language=Spanish|publisher=Compa\u00f1\u00eda Period\u00edstica Nacional}}</ref>\n\n===Awards===\nWinners are listed first and highlighted with '''boldface'''.<ref name=Ariel-Nominees-2016/><ref>{{cite news|title=Lista de ganadores de los Premios Ariel|url=http://www.eluniversal.com.mx/articulo/espectaculos/cine/2016/05/28/lista-de-ganadores-de-los-premios-ariel-2016|accessdate=October 31, 2016|work=El Universal|date=May 28, 2016}}</ref>\n{| class=wikitable\n|-\n|  style=\"vertical-align:top; width:50%;\"|\n{{Award category|#EEDD82|[[Ariel Award for Best Picture|Best Picture]]}}\n* '''''[[The Chosen Ones (2015 film)|Las Elegidas]]'' \u2013 Canana and Manny Films'''\n** ''[[600 Miles|600 Millas]]'' \u2013 Luc\u00eda Films\n** ''[[Gloria (2014 film)|Gloria]]'' \u2013 Pelo Suelo Mexico Films and R\u00edo Negro\n** ''[[The Thin Yellow Line|La Delgada L\u00ednea Amarilla]]'' \u2013 Springall Pictures\n** ''[[Un Monstruo de Mil Cabezas]]'' \u2013 Buena Ventura Producciones\n|  style=\"vertical-align:top; width:50%;\"|\n{{Award category|#EEDD82|[[Ariel Award for Best Direction|Best Director]]}}\n* '''[[David Pablos]]&nbsp;\u2013 ''[[The Chosen Ones (2015 film)|Las Elegidas]]'''''\n** [[Julio Hern\u00e1ndez Cord\u00f3n]]&nbsp;\u2013 ''[[Te Prometo Anarqu\u00eda]]''\n** [[Rodrigo Pl\u00e1]]&nbsp;\u2013 ''[[Un Monstruo de Mil Cabezas]]''\n** [[Gabriel Ripstein]]&nbsp;\u2013 ''[[600 Miles|600 Millas]]''\n** Anwar Safa&nbsp;\u2013 ''[[El Jerem\u00edas]]''\n|-\n|  style=\"vertical-align:top; width:50%;\"|\n{{Award category|#EEDD82|[[Ariel Award for Best Actor|Best Actor]]}}\n* '''[[Marco P\u00e9rez (actor)|Marco P\u00e9rez]]&nbsp;\u2013 ''[[Gloria (2014 film)|Gloria]]'' as Sergio Andrade'''\n** [[Dami\u00e1n Alc\u00e1zar]]&nbsp;\u2013 ''[[The Thin Yellow Line|La Delgada L\u00ednea Amarilla]]'' as To\u00f1o\n** [[Kristyan Ferrer]]&nbsp;\u2013 ''[[600 Miles|600 Millas]]'' as Arnulfo Rubio\n** [[Tenoch Huerta Mej\u00eda|Tenoch Huerta]]&nbsp;\u2013 ''[[El M\u00e1s Buscado|Mexican Gangster: La Leyenda del Charro Misterioso]]'' as Charro Misterioso / Alfredo R\u00edos Galeana\n** [[Tim Roth]]&nbsp;\u2013 ''[[600 Miles|600 Millas]]'' as Hank Harris\n|  style=\"vertical-align:top; width:50%;\"|\n{{Award category|#EEDD82|[[Ariel Award for Best Actress|Best Actress]]}}\n* '''[[Sof\u00eda Espinosa]]&nbsp;\u2013 ''[[Gloria (2014 film)|Gloria]]'' as [[Gloria Trevi]]'''\n** [[Geraldine Chaplin]]&nbsp;\u