op\" |\n{{Award category|#EEDD82|Best Costume Design}}\n* '''''[[El M\u00e1s Buscado|Mexican Gangster: La Leyenda del Charro Misterioso]]''&nbsp;\u2013 Gilda Navarro'''\n** ''[[Gloria (2014 film)|Gloria]]''&nbsp;\u2013 Gilda Navarro\n** ''Hilda''&nbsp;\u2013 M\u00f3nica Neumaier\n** ''[[The Thin Yellow Line|La Delgada L\u00ednea Amarilla]]''&nbsp;\u2013 Gabriela Fern\u00e1ndez\n** ''[[The Chosen Ones (2015 film)|Las Elegidas]]''&nbsp;\u2013 Daniela Schneider\n|-\n| valign=\"top\" |\n{{Award category|#EEDD82|Best Special Effects}}\n* '''''[[El M\u00e1s Buscado|Mexican Gangster: La Leyenda del Charro Misterioso]]''&nbsp;\u2013 Alejandro V\u00e1zquez'''\n** ''[[600 Miles|600 Millas]]''&nbsp;\u2013 Alejandro V\u00e1zquez\n** ''Alicia en el Pa\u00eds de Mar\u00eda''&nbsp;\u2013 Ricardo Arvizu\n** ''Familia Gang''&nbsp;\u2013 Jos\u00e9 \u00c1ngel Cordero\n** ''[[The Thin Yellow Line|La Delgada L\u00ednea Amarilla]]''&nbsp;\u2013 Alejandro V\u00e1zquez\n| valign=\"top\" |\n{{Award category|#EEDD82|Best Visual Effects}}\n* '''''[[El M\u00e1s Buscado|Mexican Gangster: La Leyenda del Charro Misterioso]]''&nbsp;\u2013 Charlie Iturriaga and Natalia de la Garza'''\n** ''[[600 Miles|600 Millas]]''&nbsp;\u2013 Edgardo Mej\u00eda\n** ''[[El Jerem\u00edas]]''&nbsp;\u2013 Ra\u00fal Prado, Edgar Pi\u00f1a and Juan Carlos Lepe\n** ''[[Gloria (2014 film)|Gloria]]''&nbsp;\u2013 Ra\u00fal Prado, Edgar Pi\u00f1a and Juan Carlos Lepe\n** ''[[The Thin Yellow Line|La Delgada L\u00ednea Amarilla]]''&nbsp;\u2013 Miguel de Hoyos, Ricardo Villarreal and Marco Rodr\u00edguez\n|}\n\n===Golden Ariel===\n*[[Rosita Quintana]]\n*[[Paul Leduc (film director)|Paul Leduc]]\n\n==Multiple nominations and awards==\n\n{{Col-begin}}\n{{Col-1-of-2}}\nThe following twelve films received multiple nominations:\n{| class=\"wikitable plainrowheaders\" rowspan=2 style=\"text-align: center;\" border=\"2\" cellpadding=\"4\" background: #f6e39c;\n|-\n! scope=\"col\" width=\"55\" | Nominations\n! scope=\"col\" align=\"center\" | Film\n|-\n! scope=row rowspan=2 style=\"text-align:center\" | 14\n| ''[[Gloria (2014 film)|Gloria]]''\n|-\n| ''[[The Thin Yellow Line|La Delgada L\u00ednea Amarilla]]''\n|-\n! scope=row rowspan=2 style=\"text-align:center\" | 13\n| ''[[600 Miles|600 Millas]]''\n|-\n| ''[[The Chosen Ones (2015 film)|Las Elegidas]]''\n|-\n! scope=row rowspan=1 style=\"text-align:center\" | 9\n| ''[[El Jerem\u00edas]]''\n|-\n! scope=row rowspan=1 style=\"text-align:center\" | 8\n| ''[[El M\u00e1s Buscado|Mexican Gangster: La Leyenda del Charro Misterioso]]''\n|-\n! scope=row rowspan=1 style=\"text-align:center\" | 7\n| ''[[Un Monstruo de Mil Cabezas]]''\n|-\n! scope=row rowspan=1 style=\"text-align:center\" | 5\n| ''Hilda''\n|-\n! scope=row rowspan=1 style=\"text-align:center\" | 3\n| ''[[Sand Dollars (film)|D\u00f3lares de Arena]]''\n|-\n! scope=row rowspan=3 style=\"text-align:center\" | 2\n| ''El Hombre Que Vio Demasiado''\n|-\n| ''[[Sopladora de Hojas]]''\n|-\n| ''[[I Promise You Anarchy|Te Prometo Anarqu\u00eda]]''\n|}\n{{Col-2-of-2}}\nFilms that received multiple awards:\n{| class=\"wikitable plainrowheaders\" rowspan=2 style=\"text-align: center;\" border=\"2\" cellpadding=\"4\" background: #f6e39c;\n|-\n! scope=\"col\" width=\"55\" | Awards\n! scope=\"col\" align=\"center\" | Film\n|-\n! scope=row rowspan=2 style=\"text-align:center\" | 5\n| ''[[Gloria (2014 film)|Gloria]]''\n|-\n| ''[[The Chosen Ones (2015 film)|Las Elegidas]]''\n|-\n! scope=row rowspan=1 style=\"text-align:center\" | 4\n| ''[[El M\u00e1s Buscado|Mexican Gangster: La Leyenda del Charro Misterioso]]''\n|-\n! scope=row rowspan=2 style=\"text-align:center\" | 2\n| ''[[600 Miles|600 Millas]]''\n|-\n| ''El Hombre Que Vio Demasiado''\n|-\n|}\n{{Col-end}}\n\n==Ceremony information==\nThe Mexican Academy of Film Arts and Sciences (AMACC) registered 152 films to compete for the Ariel Awards of 2016 in 26 categories, an increase of 11% from 2015.<ref name=Ariel-Registro-152>{{cite news|url=http://www.cronica.com.mx/notas/2016/950182.html|title=Premios Ariel anuncian pel\u00edculas preseleccionadas|date=March 13, 2016|accessdate=April 19, 2016|work=Cr\u00f3nica|language=Spanish|publisher=La Cr\u00f3nica Diaria}}</ref><ref name=Ariel-CineTOMA>{{cite news|url=https://revistatoma.wordpress.com/tag/candidatos/|title=Lista completa de candidatos y ganadores del LVIII Ariel|date=April 13, 2016|accessdate=April 19, 2016|work=Cine Toma|language=Spanish}}</ref> The films comprised were 71 feature films (including twelve documentaries and nine animated films) and 13 films for the Best Iberoamerican Feature Film.<ref name=Ariel-CineTOMA/> For the [[Ariel Award for Best Picture|Best Picture]] award, 41 films were considered, as they meet the requirement of having commercial exhibition in cinemas in Mexico or been exhibited at international film festivals in 2015.<ref name=Ariel-Registro-152/><ref name=Ariel-CineTOMA/> The AMACC created a committee of 189 people, who were active members and previous Ariel Award nominees and winners to vote for the 2015 nominees.<ref name=Ariel-Registro-152/><ref name=Ariel-CineTOMA/> To promote the award ceremony, a photo exhibition showing the actresses awarded the [[Ariel Award for Best Actress|Ariel for Best Lead Actress]] was inaugurated on May 2, 2016 at the gates of the [[Chapultepec|Bosque de Chapultepec]].<ref name=Ariel-Nominees-ElUniversal/> An official tour titled \"Rumbo al Ariel\" showed the nominated films on movie theaters in Mexico City, including the Cineteca Nacional, Cineman\u00eda Loreto and Cine Tonal\u00e1, among others.<ref name=Ariel-Nominees-ElUniversal/> Three nominated films have had a successful runs on international film festivals. ''[[The Chosen Ones (2015 film)|Las Elegidas]]'' was included in the selection for the [[Un Certain Regard]] at the [[2015 Cannes Film Festival|68th Cannes Film Festival]].<ref name=Ariel-Nominees-2016/> ''[[600 Miles|600 Millas]]'' was awarded the Best First Feature Award at the [[65th Berlin International Film Festival]] and was selected to represent [[List of Mexican submissions for the Academy Award for Best Foreign Language Film|Mexico]] for the [[List of submissions to the 88th Academy Awards for Best Foreign Language Film|88th Academy Awards]]; the box office performance in the country was \"discreet\", according to newspaper ''[[El Pa\u00eds]]'' with 92,000 attendees.<ref name=Ariel-Nominees-ElPais>{{cite news|url=http://cultura.elpais.com/cultura/2016/04/14/actualidad/1460596074_588745.html|title=Tres \u00f3peras primas parten como favoritas de los premios Ariel|date=April 13, 2016|accessdate=April 19, 2016|work=El Pa\u00eds|last=Beauregard|first=Luis Pablo|language=Spanish|publisher=PRISA}}</ref> ''[[The Thin Yellow Line|La Delgada L\u00ednea Amarilla]]'' was named Best Iberoamerican Film and the Bronze Zenith Award for The Best First Fiction Feature Film at the [[Montreal World Film Festival]].<ref name=Ariel-Nominees-2016/><ref name=Ariel-Nominees-ElPais/> Meanwhile, ''[[Gloria (2014 film)|Gloria]]'', a biopic about Mexican singer-songwriter [[Gloria Trevi]], was premiered in 2014, but formalities presented by the Mexican Academy prevented it to be postulated that year.<ref name=Ariel-Nominees-ElPais/>\n\n===Box office performance of nominees===\nAt the time of the nominations announcement on April 13, the highest earner among the nominated films was ''[[Un gallo con muchos huevos|Un Gallo con Muchos Huevos]]'' with MXN$167.8 million in domestic box office receipts, and also was the highest-grossing film of 2015 in Mexico.<ref name=BoxOfficeAriel>{{cite news|title=Las 10 pel\u00edculas mexicanas m\u00e1s taquilleras del 2015: Un Gallo..., El Gran Peque\u00f1o, A la mala...|url=http://aristeguinoticias.com/3112/kiosko/las-10-peliculas-mexicanas-mas-taquilleras-del-2015-videos/|date=December 31, 2015|accessdate=April 20, 2016|work=Aristegui Noticias|language=Spanish}}</ref> Only one Best Picture nominee ranked at the top ten, ''Gloria'', at number five with MXN$34.9 million.<ref name=BoxOfficeAriel/> At number seven, ''Elvira, te dar\u00eda mi vida pero la estoy usando'', with earnings of MXN$23.0 million, was nominated for Best Supporting Actress.<ref name=BoxOfficeAriel/> As for the rest of the Best Picture nominated films, ''Las Elegidas'' had its commercial release in theaters in Mexico on April 22 and was made available for streaming via [[Netflix]] on May 8.<ref name=BoxOfficeElegidasEstreno>{{cite news|title=Las elegidas, una historia desgarradora estrena el 22 de abril|url=http://www.imcine.gob.mx/comunicacion-social/comunicados-y-noticias/las-elegidas-una-historia-desgarradora-estrena-el-22-de-abril|accessdate=April 20, 2016|date=April 13, 2016|publisher=Instituto Mexicano de Cinematograf\u00eda|language=Spanish}}</ref><ref name=BoxOfficeElegidasEstrenoNetflix>{{cite news|title=La cruda cinta Las elegidas llega a Netflix a unos d\u00edas de su estreno en cines|url=http://de10.com.mx/top-10/2016/04/26/la-cruda-cinta-las-elegidas-llega-netflix-unos-dias-de-su-estreno-en-cines|accessdate=May 11, 2016|date=April 26, 2016|work=El Universal|language=Spanish}}</ref> ''600 Millas'' earned MXN$4.4 million in Mexico.<ref name=BoxOffice600>{{cite news|title=600 Millas|url=http://www.boxofficemojo.com/movies/?page=intl&id=600millas.htm|accessdate=April 20, 2016|publisher=Box Office Mojo}}</ref>\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist|30em}}\n\n{{Ariel Awards |state=autocollapse}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Ariel Awards, 58}}\n[[Category:Ariel Awards ceremonies]]\n[[Category:2016 film awards]]\n[[Category:2016 in Mexican cinema]]\n", "text_old": "{{Use mdy dates|date=January 2017}}\n{{Infobox film awards\n| number           = 58\n| award            = Ariel Awards\n| image            = Official Poster - Ariel Awards 2016.jpg\n| caption          = Official poster\n| date             = May 28, 2016\n| site             = [[National Auditorium]]<br>[[Mexico City]], Mexico\n| host             = \n| producer         = \n| director         = \n| best_picture     = ''[[The Chosen Ones (2015 film)|Las Elegidas]]''\n| most_wins        = ''Las Elegidas'' and ''[[Gloria (2014 film)|Gloria]]'' (5)\n| most_nominations = ''[[The Thin Yellow Line|La Delgada L\u00ednea Amarilla]]'' and ''Gloria'' (14)\n| network          = [[Canal Once (Mexico)|Canal Once]]\n| duration         = \n| ratings          = \n| last             = [[57th Ariel Awards|57th]]\n| next             = [[59th Ariel Awards|59th]]\n}}\n\nThe '''58th Ariel Awards''' ceremony, organized by the [[Academia Mexicana de Artes y Ciencias Cinematogr\u00e1ficas|Mexican Academy of Film Arts and Sciences]] (AMACC) took take place on May 28, 2016, at the [[National Auditorium]] in [[Mexico City]]. During the ceremony, AMACC presented the [[Ariel Award]] in 26 categories honoring [[2015 in film|films released in 2015]]. The ceremony, was televised in Mexico by [[Canal Once (Mexico)|Canal Once]].<ref name=Ariel-Nominees-2016>{{cite news|url=http://www.cinepremiere.com.mx/58431-nominados-al-ariel-2016.html|title=Nominados al Ariel 2016|date=April 13, 2016|accessdate=April 13, 2016|work=Cine Premiere|last=Maga\u00f1a|first=Arturo|language=Spanish}}</ref>\n\n''[[The Chosen Ones (2015 film)|Las Elegidas]]'', and ''[[Gloria (2014 film)|Gloria]]'' each won five awards, with the former earning the [[Ariel Award for Best Picture|Best Picture]] honor. Other winners included ''[[El M\u00e1s Buscado|Mexican Gangster: La Leyenda del Charro Misterioso]]'' with four; ''[[600 Miles|600 Millas]]'', and ''El Hombre Que Vio Demasiado'' with two; and ''Ausencias'', ''[[Embrace of the Serpent|El Abrazo de la Serpiente]]'', ''[[El Jerem\u00edas]]'', ''Hilda'', ''La Incre\u00edble Historia del Ni\u00f1o de Piedra'', ''[[Un Monstruo de Mil Cabezas]]'', ''Tr\u00e9mulo'', and ''Zimbo'' with one.\n\n==Winners and nominees==\nThe nominees for the 58th Ariel Awards were announced on April 13, 2016 at the Cineteca Nacional in Mexico City, by [[Dolores Heredia]], president of the Academy, and actors [[Adriana Paz]] and [[Juan Manuel Bernal]], winners for Best Actress and Best Actor, respectively, at the [[57th Ariel Awards]].<ref name=Ariel-Nominees-2016/> ''[[The Thin Yellow Line|La Delgada L\u00ednea Amarilla]]'' and ''[[Gloria (2014 film)|Gloria]]'' received the most nominations with fourteen; ''[[600 Miles|600 Millas]]'' and ''[[The Chosen Ones (2015 film)|Las Elegidas]]'' came in second with thirteen apiece.<ref name=Ariel-Nominees-2016/> The [[Golden Ariel]] was awarded to actress [[Rosita Quintana]] and film director [[Paul Leduc (film director)|Paul Leduc]].<ref name=Ariel-Nominees-2016/> The ceremony was held at the [[National Auditorium]] in Mexico City for the first time, instead of its traditional venue, [[Palacio de Bellas Artes]], in order to increase the capacity to 2,300 seats, according to Heredia.<ref name=Ariel-Nominees-ElUniversal>{{cite news|url=http://www.eluniversal.com.mx/articulo/espectaculos/cine/2016/04/13/anuncian-cintas-nominadas-al-ariel-2016|title=Anuncia cintas nominadas al Ariel 2016|date=April 13, 2016|accessdate=April 19, 2016|work=El Universal|last=Huerta|first=Cesar|language=Spanish|publisher=Compa\u00f1\u00eda Period\u00edstica Nacional}}</ref>\n\n===Awards===\nWinners are listed first and highlighted with '''boldface'''.<ref name=Ariel-Nominees-2016/><ref>{{cite news|title=Lista de ganadores de los Premios Ariel|url=http://www.eluniversal.com.mx/articulo/espectaculos/cine/2016/05/28/lista-de-ganadores-de-los-premios-ariel-2016|accessdate=October 31, 2016|work=El Universal|date=May 28, 2016}}</ref>\n{| class=wikitable\n|-\n|  style=\"vertical-align:top; width:50%;\"|\n{{Award category|#EEDD82|[[Ariel Award for Best Picture|Best Picture]]}}\n* '''''[[The Chosen Ones (2015 film)|Las Elegidas]]'' \u2013 Canana and Manny Films'''\n** ''[[600 Miles|600 Millas]]'' \u2013 Luc\u00eda Films\n** ''[[Gloria (2014 film)|Gloria]]'' \u2013 Pelo Suelo Mexico Films and R\u00edo Negro\n** ''[[The Thin Yellow Line|La Delgada L\